    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hey @krasi-georgiev, \r\n\r\nUnfortunately, we can't guarantee that Hardhat Network has the same gas costs as every evm chain. If the C-Chain has the same gas costs as mainnet, and you set the Hardhat Network `hardfork` config to match the C-Chain's they'll match, otherwise they won't. IMHO changing the gas costs in an EVM network is a mistake, as there are tons of small incompatibilities that you introduce by doing so.",
